<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,288,678,704]" box="[189,288,678,704]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,288,678,704]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,288,678,704]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Ecology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1398,723,783]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Like other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[455,628,723,749]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[455,628,723,749]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Ameroglossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix" authorityYear="2021" box="[867,1019,723,749]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulniorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[867,1019,723,749]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">A. fulniorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1029,1123,723,749]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is restricted to granite outcrops. Flowering and fruiting in August.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,475,821,847]" box="[189,475,821,847]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,475,821,847]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,475,821,847]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Population and threats</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1400,866,996]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Only two populations of 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix" authorityYear="2021" box="[520,678,866,892]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulniorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[520,678,866,892]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">A. fulniorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[694,794,867,893]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are currently known, which together comprise approximately 40 widely spaced adult individuals. Due to the isolation of those populations and their restricted distributions, together with environmental pressure from trampling by domestic animals and the occasional passage of wildfires, this species is highly threatened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
